{
  "texts": [
    "This approach is conceptually similar to causal language modeling 66, with the important difference that the inputs and outputs are continuous values, rather than (probabilities over) discrete tokens.",
    "This model is trained using the same dataset and data splits as our main FoldingDiff model with the same preprocessing and normalization.",
    "We train f AR using the AdamW optimizer with weight decay set to 0.01.",
    "We use a batch size of 256 over 10,000 epochs, linearly scaling the learning rate from 0 to 5 × 10 À5 over the first 1000 epochs, and back to 0 over the remaining 9000 epochs.",
    "We find that the validation loss does not improve beyond 1446 epochs of training, and use this model checkpoint for generation."
  ]
}